This file resides in <ambulant-topdir>/installers/nokia770

This directory is intended to contain all stuff needed to produce
an installer for the nokia 770/N800 (OS2008 'Chinook' release)

On 'Chinook' scratchbox, download Ambulant source tree in <ambulant-topdir>.
In <ambulant-topdir>/src/third_party_packages, download and install ffmpeg:

svn checkout -r "{2008-06-15}" svn://svn.mplayerhq.hu/ffmpeg/trunk ffmpeg 
./configure --cpu=arm1136jf-s --enable-cross-compile
make

At this moment, I'm unsure whether the value for --cpu=
is really the right one, at least it now compiles and runs.

In <ambulant-topdir>, configure and build AmbulantPlayer:
./configure --prefix=/usr --with-qt=no --with-gtk --with-nokia770\
	 --host=i386 --with-ffmpeg --build=arm --with-gsteamer
make

In <ambulant-topdir>/installers/nokia770, run: ./create_installer
A debian package (.deb) will be made in <ambulant-topdir>/installers,
which, when copied to a website, can be installed on a Nokia machine,
where it thereafter can be found in 'Extras'.

Currently, AmbulantPlayer works with the following limitations:
- the GUI is not 'hildonized'
- video is not working properly (far too slow or hangs)
- rtsp is not implemented
- No logging
- No preferences
- No xerces
- Often crashes after playing 1 or 2 files

Kees Blom, Feb. 5th, 2007
Updates:   Nov. 3th, 2008


